Create iso file from cd/dvd:
Unmount cd/dvd: umount /dev/sr0
Get block/volume size: sudo isoinfo -d -i /dev/sr0 | grep -i -E 'block size|volume size'
Create the iso: dd if=/dev/sr0 of=name.iso bs=<block number from above command> count=<volume number from above command> status=progress

Pull BIOS embedded key:
sudo strings /sys/firmware/acpi/tables/MSDM

Set virsh editor:

touch ~/.selected_editor
nano ~/.selected_editor
Add SELECTED_EDITOR=/usr/bin/micro
Exit and save the file

Commands to check and edit the virtual bridge NIC:

List default info: virsh net-list

Show default config:  virsh net-dumpxml default

Edit default config: virsh net-edit default

Stop default config: virsh net-destroy default

Start default config: virsh net-start default

.bash_aliases file:
alias cls=/usr/bin/clear
alias nano=/usr/bin/micro
alias py=/usr/bin/python3
